                <summary>Frederick S. Tukey is disputing the results of the election for the
                    Convention by questioning the counting of the ballots cast for James C.
                    Southall. Thomas P. Jackson, head of the Board of Registration for Augusta,
                    filed a report in the matter.</summary>
