                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper reports that "the thorough organization of the Conservatives in
                    Augusta county is progressing rapidly but quietly. Look out for a 'vote as is a
                    vote' against the Constitution."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper complains that the Street Cleaning Ordinance is not enforced.
                    "Piles of dirt lay in the middle of the Streets for days."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper jokes that the "'epidemic matrimonial' is raging so fearfully in
                    the Great Valley at present, that it taxes our utmost powers to keep a fair
                    record of its terrible devastation. There seems to be no danger of the race
                    dying out."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
